The paper deals with the problem of detecting malicious behavior in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.CR). The proposed protocol involves monitoring downstream neighbors, which is a key aspect of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of a trellis structure for the graphical model suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY).
